### Pre-deployment Checklist
- [ ] `requirements.txt` is up to date (or dependencies in `pyproject.toml`)
- [ ] Entrypoint (`app.py`) exports `app` instance
- [ ] All secrets in environment variables (not hardcoded)
- [ ] `DEBUG = False` in production config
- [ ] Database connection pooling configured
- [ ] CORS configured for frontend origin
- [ ] Health check endpoint exists (`/health`)
- [ ] Error handlers registered
- [ ] Bundle size < 250MB (ideally < 50MB)

## Performance Best Practices

### Response Times
- Target: < 200ms for simple CRUD
- Target: < 500ms for complex queries
- Target: < 1s for aggregate operations

### Cold Start Optimization
- Minimize top-level imports
- Use lightweight dependencies
- Lazy-load heavy modules
- Keep bundle size small (< 50MB ideal)

### Database Performance
- Use indexes on frequently queried columns
- Avoid N+1 queries (use `joinedload`)
- Use pagination for list endpoints
- Configure connection pooling for serverless

### Caching
```python
# Use flask-caching for response caching
from flask_caching import Cache
cache = Cache(config={"CACHE_TYPE": "SimpleCache"})

@app.route("/api/v1/stats")
@cache.cached(timeout=300)  # Cache for 5 minutes
def get_stats():
    return jsonify(compute_stats())
```

## Security Checklist

- [ ] JWT tokens validated and expired properly
- [ ] Passwords hashed with bcrypt or argon2
- [ ] CORS restricted to allowed origins
- [ ] Rate limiting on auth endpoints
- [ ] Input validated with Pydantic
- [ ] SQL injection prevented (use ORM, never raw SQL with user input)
- [ ] Secrets in environment variables
- [ ] HTTPS enforced (Vercel handles this)
- [ ] Error messages don't leak internal details
- [ ] File uploads validated and size-limited (if applicable)

