## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ DON'T: Global app object
```python
app = Flask(__name__)  # Global, hard to test
```

### ✅ DO: Application factory
```python
def create_app(config="default"):
    app = Flask(__name__)
    return app
```

### ❌ DON'T: Business logic in routes
```python
@app.route("/users", methods=["POST"])
def create_user():
    # 50 lines of logic here
```

### ✅ DO: Service layer
```python
@api_bp.route("/users", methods=["POST"])
def create_user():
    data = UserCreate.model_validate(request.get_json())
    user = UserService.create(data)
    return jsonify(UserResponse.model_validate(user).model_dump()), 201
```

### ❌ DON'T: Skip input validation
```python
data = request.get_json()
user = User(email=data["email"])  # No validation!
```

### ✅ DO: Pydantic validation
```python
data = UserCreate.model_validate(request.get_json())  # Validates!
```

### ❌ DON'T: Hardcode secrets
```python
SECRET_KEY = "my-super-secret-key"
```

### ✅ DO: Environment variables
```python
SECRET_KEY = os.environ.get("SECRET_KEY")
```
